      "id": "PopularPost115011",
      "post_content": "So much better than [Lava Axe](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lava Axe)! I can't imagine why this wouldn't be in something like a red EDH, where someone is bound to have more life than you. Recurrable damage can be so devastating when card advantage really counts. Sadly, this just wouldn't make it in today's red decks - if your opponent isn't 7-10 damage below you by turn three, you're doing something wrong :3",
