    {
      "id": "PopularPost47300",
      "post_content": "Mdak, since this card is an instant, even on 6th turn, if you're untapped (which for red WAS highly unlikely) you could burn them for 8 and maybe bring them down to fireball range. Being able to smack them in the mouth for 4 at the end of every one of their turns until the life totals equaled for a measly cost of 3 mana was ridiculous. Pulse of the Fields being the reverse of this, but good still.",
      "posted_by": "Penultimate",
